FROM ORIGINAL CODE
Evolution attempt from goblin/p2pool-stats.

node.js is a fine solution for the aim of the stats, BUT tailing P2Pool's log has a high I/O price.
This is an attempt at creating a node.js with JSON listeners, than can receive POST information from whatever you wish.

There's even a possibility to have MySQL doing JSON POSTs on INSERT or UPDATE - tested, still not very efficient, will come later if I can raise its performance.

The chain_img, albeit "nice", might be a bit heavy on slow connections, so it will become optional too.


